M|references|| a myriad of | many, numerous, various |
M|references|| a plethora of | many, numerous, several |
M|references|| paramount | very important, essential, critical |
M|references|| pertaining to | about, regarding, concerning |
M|references|| prior to | before |
M|references|| subsequent to | after |
M|references|| in light of | because of, given, considering |
M|references|| with respect to | about, regarding, for |
M|references|| in terms of | regarding, for, about |
M|references|| the fact that | that (or rewrite sentence) |
M|references|1. Read your text aloud. If phrases sound unnatural in speech, revise them
M|references|2. Ask: "Would I say this in a conversation with a colleague?"
M|references|3. Check for repetitive sentence structures
M|references|4. Look for clusters of the words listed above
M|references|5. Ensure varied sentence lengths (not all similar length)
M|references|6. Verify each intensifier adds genuine meaning